						               													<description>Blood, Bilge and Iron Balls is a set of wargame rules for naval battles in the Age of Sail.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;With them you can recreate the triumphs of Nelson or Hawke or tackle pirates on the Spanish Main.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The rules themselves are very simple and easy to learn.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player can easily command a single ship or several, the rules working equally well for a single frigate chasing down a privateer, or a large-scale fleet action with multiple players on each side.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The basic rules have been written with the emphasis on providing a fast-playing and fun game, but optional rules are included which will add a greater level of historical realism and detail.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A unique card-driven turn sequence prevents the game becoming too predictable.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Also included are a selection of scenarios for re-fighting specific historical battles and simple campaign rules.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Although intended for use with model ships, the rule book includes sheets of ship counters which can be used to get started.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Just add dice, tape measure and pencil and you're ready to play.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
